And then 5 minutes later if you hype yourself and listen to a different track you can easily lift it in spite of being more exhausted. Many things, be it survival or weightlifting, are surprisingly psychological. It's always the mind that either gives up or disciplines the flesh.

Watching Les Stroud survival videos and it's interesting how important the psychological aspect is, e.g. lighting a fire is helpful even just because seeing it motivates you not to give up. Very similar to weightlifting where a weight might not even budge at the first attempt ...

I really like that St. Paisios quote about t-shirts with images of saints or cathedrals or such being ok to wear if done well, because it's the type of thing where we would overcorrect and assume it must be 100% sacrilegious because we are way too neurotic about this kinda stuff.

Sort of like that story of Fr. Seraphim Rose getting annoyed with some monks who were overdoing the lenten fast and almost ruined their health because they were basically eating nothing so he proceeded to make a giant peanut butter sandwich and then consumed it in front of them.
